OL,3,CBBC confirms changes to BBC News
OL,4,Coutput in the coming year
OL,6,
OL,7,F Newsnight will be downgraded to a 30-
OL,8,Fminute discussion and interview
OL,9,Fprogramme, but will continue to
OL,10,Fbroadcast on weeknights on BBC Two.
OL,11,F The BBC News at One will move to
OL,12,FSalford in the new year, extending its
OL,13,Fbroadcast time to one hour.
OL,14,F Meanwhile, BBC Breakfast will be
OL,15,Fextended by 15 minutes ` that's less
OL,16,Fthan the 45-minute extension to 10am
OL,17,Fthat had once been mooted.
OL,18,F Over on the BBC's News Channel,
OL,19,Fcurrent affairs documentary strand Our
OL,20,FWorld is cancelled, leaving the BBC
OL,21,Fwith more weekend airtime to be filled
OL,22,Fwith something else.
OL,23,F A number of reporter roles will
OL,24,Fclose, although some new posts will be
OL,25,Fcreated in other parts of BBC News.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/8
